snippet.textDisplay:
Martin was known at the time (90s) to have erratic behavior and there were many reports saying Tisha was not happy working on the Martin show in the later seasons. Yes there was a sexual harassment lawsuit and it was settled out of court. Looks like Martin grew from that experience and payed the price for it. Tbh his ego is bigger than it should be; he held out of Bad Boys 3 for a long time due to want more money (presumably more than Will Smith). So when people bring it up he might’ve felt embarrassed by it. Eddie Murphy made homophobic jokes in the 80s and he acknowledged that it was a mistakes and regretted it way before this woke or cancel culture.

If this comes up again Martin should face it head on and acknowledge the situation and that he has grown from it. Dissing something serious like that despite the me too movement just shows he’s not entirely over it. Tisha looks like she moved on and both made amends.
